channel.title: Neo-Account Maker
channel.description:
I'm looking to make a Neopets account maker.
Problem is, I don't know how to randomize keystrokes.
I figure that if I have about 10-15 letters and numbers, randomly put into the username box, I can (hopefully) get an available username with each try.
But how can I randomize a set of keystrokes?
Please help.
:) Merry Christmas! :)

item.title: Neo-Account Maker
item.dc:creator: @bullzeye95 bullzeye
item.description:
@bullzeye95 wrote:

[scar]program New;
var
i: integer;
character: array of string;

procedure setItUp;
begin
character:= [‘a’,‘b’,‘c’,‘d’,‘e’,‘f’,‘g’,‘h’,‘i’,‘j’,‘k’,‘l’,‘m’,‘n’,‘o’,‘p’,‘q’,‘r’,‘s’,‘t’,‘u’,‘v’,‘w’,‘x’,‘y’,‘z’,‘1’,‘2’,‘3’,‘4’,‘5’,‘6’,‘7’,‘8’,‘9’,‘0’];
end;

begin
setItUp;
for i:= 1 to 5 do
sendkeys(character[1+random(36)]);
end.[/scar]
